response.title: Little Shop Of Horrors
response.description: Feed me! This is Roger Corman's original comic horror story of Audrey, the talking, man-eating plant, her owner, a sadistic dentist and his pain loving patient, played by Jack Nicholson. Remade, as a musical starring Steve Marvin, by the team behind Ghostbusters.

response.title: Freak
response.description: It was twenty-five years ago that the horror began a hideously, physically deformed and brutalised 9-year old boy murders his tyrannical and abusing mother. Now the horror is about to start all over again, but even more frightening and blood-thirsty than before as the homocidal monstrosity has just escaped from a maximum security prison for the mentally insane.

response.title: Letters From A Killer
response.description: Race Darnell sits on death row for a felony he didn't commit and passes the time by corresponding with four lonesome ladies via tape-recorded letters. When the tapes get sent to the wrong pen pals, one woman decides the two-timing Darnell must die. Eventually acquitted of the murder he's serving time for, Darnell gets released ...and ends up in a cat-and-mouse game with a killer determined to exact revenge for her broken heart.

response.title: The Return Of The Swamp Thing
response.description: The monster at the bottom of the mucky waters is back in this sequel to the campy horror classic. This time, the Swamp Thing is a hero of sorts, rescuing an attractive horticulturist (Heather Locklear) from her dastardly stepfather (Louis Jourdan), whom she suspects is behind her mother's early and mysterious death

response.title: La Cucaracha
response.description: A desperate writer fights for survival when the Mexican mob involves him in murder.

response.title: Headhunter
response.description: The best way to get ahead in business is to keep your own Ambitious young go-getter Ben Caruso signs on with sexy corporate headhunter Sarah Tierney, who finds him a great job with great pay and only one drawback. Its the graveyard shift. Not a problem. Ben accepts the job as well as Sarahs sexual advances. Professional reasons aside, this is one line Ben should never have crossed. He quickly learns that his coworkers are actually the tormented souls of Sarahs previous conquests, and that his real job is to find a missing heador looose with each tick of the clock. Ben comes ever-closer to either locating the head or ending up on the chopping block himself. Looks like the best way to get ahead in business is to keep your own.

response.title: Dunsmore
response.description: Dunsmore is a quiet one-road town in the backwoods of Florida, too far off the Interstate to matter. When local bully Ronny Roy Pritcher is brutally murdered, the media descends on this small town, and Special Investigator Walter Taylor is sent in to question the local townspeople. At first no one will talk to an outsiderbut gradually Taylor learns the details of Pritchers sadistic reign of terror and the horrifying events leading up to his death.

response.title: Bloody Mary
response.description: Chanting Bloody Mary at a psychiatric hospital hardly seems like a good idea. But good sense doesn't stop three nurses from raising the evil that may be more than urban legend. This horror film brings the mythic murderess to life and looses her on the staff and patients of an asylum.

response.title: 8 Million Dollars
response.description: Eight strangers arrive at a house in the woods to participate in an experiment  with a reward of 8 million dollars to divide between them  just stay in the secluded house for the entire weekend. Will they enjoy a quiet weekend at the lake, or with the table full of weapons prove to be too tempting.. At first, the group agrees to simply wait in the house until the two days are up, and each collect their one million dollars  that is, until one subject mysteriously dies, and some of the remaining subjects want to leave the house  which will void the game for all.

response.title: Aegri Somnia
response.description:
Aegri Somnia - A Sick Man's Dreams is a visual act. The film's strength is absolutely in its look, every frame is as deliberate as a piece of art. The look is reminiscent of a graphic novel, the dizzying angles, the motivated frames, every shot one that counts, the viewer a voyeur in on a conspiracy. Even the bloody scenes have an element of dream to them, as though being experienced just outside the Now, a keen memory, but a memory, the distance necessary and created, as if for our own safety. As the film drips slowly into the caustic ending, the images grow more horrible, more frightening, every one of them suitable for framing.

Susie Maloney - Author and Screenwriter of The Dwelling

response.title: Carnies
response.description:
In 1936, during the Great Depression, a traveling sideshow sets up shop to mystify yet another dustbowl town with freaks and illusions. When a sinister force begins taking the carnies lives one by one, detective Ellison is put on the case.
Is it the cryptic carnival owner, Helen What about the strong man, Virgil Or could it be Ratty, the snake handler and his friend William the sword swallower

response.title: Closet Space
response.description: What happens when the quest for knowledge comes up against the insatiable hunger for flesh Six grad students slowly and horrifically discover the answer as they search for their missing professor.

response.title: Methodic
response.description:
Demonically possessed by an ominous presence known as The Dollman , a young boy named Nicholas Matthews is forced to obey his darker half, and ultimately murders his parents. Sentenced to life under a microscope at the state mental hospital, Nicholas slowly gains control over the darkness hiding within.
But evil cannot be contained so easily. Instead, The Dollman simply bides his time, dwelling inside Nicholas, waiting for the day when he will become powerful enough to compeltely take over his human host. And when that day comes, God help us all . . .

response.title: Miyuki
response.description: Miyuki is the story of the McKenzie family who take in a young Japanese exchange student. At first their expectations of a sweet and innocent Japanese girl are realized, but soon strange things start to happen.

response.title: Underbelly
response.description: Henry Rose is a young writer who is on top of the world until his pregnant wife suddenly vanishes while admiring flowers on the side of a Texas highway. Henry races to a nearby town for help but finds the town deserted, save for a few locals who barely acknowledge his existence. Entering into town at the same time, with their own agenda, is a family of vicious psychotic criminals led by the charismatic, yet deadly Toby Haynes. When Tobys sister also disappears, he takes matters into his own hands to find the culprit. The paths of Henry and Tobys gang inevitably cross in this grim portrayal of mans descent into the unknown evils of our world.

response.title: Bloodwine
response.description:
Andrea is harassed by life, love and wicked college schoolmates.
When she is reunited with childhood friend Brandy, it is the bright spot in an otherwise morbid existence on campus. The two are drawn together when an unusual bottle of ancient origin comes between them. When one of the girls falls ill and goes on a tirade of vampiric revenge, the other must evade her long enough to solve the mystery of her illness and destroy its source.

response.title: Peter Rottentail
response.description: On a dark and stormy night, Peter Rottentail was born. Part man, part rabbit... all evil. James and Lenny thought they were fixing up a relatives newly purchased house but what they got was a weekend of horrors! What is the Evil Rabbits hidden agenda and how does it relate to a birthday party from hell years earlier Who will win the final battle between man and beast A wild mix of horror and dark comedy you will soon not forget! In the tradition of Jack Frost and Leprachaun comes Polonia Brothers latest thrill ride! Watch at your own risk!

response.title: Wicked Games
response.description: We DARE you to be a witness to the TRUE insanity of a Coppermasked Madman who systematically slaughters the sexually promiscuous and socially deviant individuals of a small Florida town. This is the exciting, twisted tale of hallucinatory eroticism and outrageous gore that is the official sequel to TRUTH OR DARE---A CRITICAL MADNESS

response.title: Separation Anxiety: Dead Bodyman 2
response.description: Eddie Benvitch, Pamela Such, Amy Lizka star. Willie is back for another round of killing and porn watching. After burying his evil twin brother in a beer cooler, Willie decided that its time to start a normal life without his brother. But, things dont always go as planned. Willie does everything he can to fight the urge to KILL again, but it isnt to long before Willie starts to seek out prostitutes and bad people to torture and kill. Plus Evil Ed has returned for revenge, God wont shut up, and Willies twin brother is on the loose again. The Meat Man is back and this time no chicken will be safe.

response.title: House Of Whipcord
response.description: Many young girls have entered these gates...none have come out. Beautiful young women are kidnapped and taken to a prison designed for the devotees of the Marquis de Sade. Guilty or not, they must be punished. The crazed caretakers viciously whip their victims in this nightmarish den of torture and depravity. Those who try to escape will be executed! British goremaster Pete Walker, Frightmare, The Flesh and Blood Show, directs this Euro Horror classic.
